title: Downtown Austin Class A Office Tower
description: This premier Class A office tower stands as a landmark in the heart of downtown Austin at 123 Congress Avenue, representing one of the city's most prestigious commercial addresses. The property is strategically located in Austin's rapidly growing tech sector, with proximity to major employers, restaurants, and entertainment venues. High-profile tenants include technology companies and professional services firms drawn to the building's modern amenities and prime location. The growing tech sector in Austin and limited Class A inventory in the downtown core present significant opportunities for continued strong performance.

The facility's proximity to the Port of Long Beach, one of the busiest ports in the United States, positions it perfectly for import/export operations. However, this location also brings regulatory considerations related to port operations and environmental compliance. The property benefits from growing e-commerce demand and increasing need for cold chain logistics, particularly in the food distribution and pharmaceutical sectors. The trust score of 88 reflects solid data verification from CBRE's internal database and Port Authority records.
